                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 36px;&quot;&gt;Step 3: View Tracked Data&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Choose the relevant tab in the Flowdometer app to view your tracking data.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Dashboards&lt;/strong&gt; tab has a long list of templates you can use.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Feel free to clone, then customize any reports you like into your own dashboards. You don&apos;t have to use them all!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 0.8125rem;&quot;&gt;Until you&apos;ve set goals, many of the charts will be blank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Flows&lt;/strong&gt; tab will show you the individual tracking records for everything being tracked.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Click on the Flow Name to view all the changes over time, tracked as child &lt;strong&gt;Step&lt;/strong&gt; records&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Flowdometer is designed to be built upon and customized. You can add your own fields to Flows and Steps, or incorporate these tracking records/fields onto whatever object you&apos;re tracking.&lt;/p&gt;</value>
